Angular Assignment - Task 1 & Task 2
Task 1: Scaffold and Explore the Angular Project

Step 1: Create Angular Project
•	npm install -g @angular/cli
•	ng version
•	ng new student-course-portal --routing --style=css
•	cd student-course-portal
•	code .
Step 2: notes.txt Content
angular.json - Project configuration.
tsconfig.json - TypeScript compiler configuration.
tsconfig.app.json - App-specific TypeScript settings.
package.json - Project metadata, dependencies and scripts.
src/main.ts - Entry point of Angular app.
src/app/app.config.ts - Application-wide configuration.
src/app/app.component.ts - Root component.
src/index.html - Main HTML page.
Step 3: Run Project
Command:
ng serve
Open http://localhost:4200
Step 4: Build Project
Command:
ng build
Compiled code is mainly inside dist/browser/main.js
Step 5: Budgets
In angular.json:
maximumWarning - Shows warning if bundle exceeds limit.
maximumError - Build fails if bundle exceeds limit.



